title: YouTube is great! Just be warned:
text:
Hi, Iâ€™ve been a user for 3 years and I have to say, YouTube is probably one of my favorite social media apps! Very inclusive and offers a wide range of topics and interests! There is a downside though. Iâ€™ll list some things below:

Negatives:
-Inappropriate content for minors and/or younger teens
(Ads for adult websites and nsfw clickbait is a common factor)
-bad camera quality
(If you create YouTube content, like I do, then I recommend not filming on the actual website. Find a different app to record on, then import the video onto YouTube. Even then, YouTube messes up the quality of it)
-toxic comments and audiences
(YouTube is a common place for toxic messages and overall just horrible people. YouTube is pretty lax on there monitoring system, so almost nothing ever gets taken down.)

Now, I know that may not seem like a big deal to some people, but itâ€™s usually younger kids and/or teens on this app. So, for any parents reading this, be careful and make sure to monitor your own kids watching limits! Now even if it seems all bad, itâ€™s still a wonderful website that allows you to find community and entertainment right at the swipe of a fingertip! Highly recommend!!!

(P.S. YouTube, please be more strict on your monitoring system, the amount of people that have nsfw content posted up is insane. Thank you)
